**Compound interest** is the engine behind long-term wealth creation. In Australia, high-interest savings accounts offer approximately 4.8–5.1% (May 2026), term deposits approximately 4.3–4.8% for 12-month terms, and a diversified share portfolio has historically returned approximately 9–10% annually (including dividends and franking credits).

This calculator handles any combination of initial deposit, regular contributions, and compounding frequency — weekly, fortnightly, monthly, quarterly, or annually. Enter an interest rate to see your final balance and total interest earned.
